Source: cinnamon-extensions
Section: gnome
Priority: extra
Maintainer: merlwiz79 <mintmerlwiz79@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7),
 cdbs,
 gnome-pkg-tools,
 intltool,
 libglib2.0-dev,
 libgtop2-dev (>= 2.28.3),
 gnome-common,
 libgnome-desktop-3-dev (>= 2.91.6)
Standards-Version: 3.9.2
Homepage: https://github.com/merlwiz79/cinnamon-extensions

Package: cinnamon-extensions-common
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon, cinnamon-session, cinnamon-settings
Description: Extensions to extend functionality of Cinnamon (common files)
 This package contains common files to be used by other individial
 extension packages.

Package: cinnamon-extensions-auto-move-windows
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon-extensions-common
Description: Auto Move Windows extension for Cinnamon
 This extension allows you to set applications to open up windows in
 separate preset workspaces rather than open windows in the current
 active workspace.

Package: cinnamon-extensions-dock
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon-extensions-common
Conflicts: cinnamon-extension-dock
Description: Dock extension for Cinnamon
 This extension shows a dock-style task switcher on the right side of the
 screen.

Package: cinnamon-extensions-drive-menu
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon-extensions-common
Description: Drive menu extension for Cinnamon
 This extension adds status menu for accessing and unmounting removable
 devices.

Package: cinnamon-extensions-places-menu
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon-extensions-common
Description: Places menu extension for Cinnamon
 This extension adds a systems status menu for quickly navigating places
 in the system.

Package: cinnamon-extensions-windows-navigator
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon-extensions-common
Description: Windows Navigator extension for Cinnamon
 This extension allows keyboard selection of windows and workspaces in the
 overview mode.

Package: cinnamon-extensions-trash
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon-extensions-common
Conflicts: cinnamon-extension-trash
Description: Trash management extension for Cinnamon
 This extension allows emptying trash and opening the trash folder
 from the panel. It hides completely when the Trash is empty.

Package: cinnamon-extensions-xrandr-indicator
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cinnamon-extensions-common, gir1.2-gnomedesktop-3.0
Description: XRandr extension to Cinnamon
 This extension adds an xrandr indicator to the Cinnamon system tray
 hence allowing the user to easily change monitor resolutions, rotate
 the desktop, manage different screens, and a lot more.
